<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="418" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/874.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">U. S. S. Des Moines</hi>, <lb/> (<hi rend="smallcaps">via wireless</hi>). <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San Juan, Porto Rico</hi>
                                </placeName> [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1913-09-16">undated</date>], <lb/>
                                (Received September 16, 1913.)</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>At Monte Cristi on September 15 I explained the attitude of the United
                            States to the Governor and citizens. The province is supporting the
                            Government and I was well received. Sent request to front Government
                            troops not to take offensive. Engagement at Navarrete the 16th
                            reported.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>